body:
The issue was encountered when I was working on fixing [Support pattern member assignment with data type #2328](https://github.com/verilator/verilator/issues/2328 ) and created this sample Test Case from IEEE 1800-2017 SV CH:10.9.2

**Example:**
```
module top();
/* verilator lint_off UNPACKED */
    typedef struct {
        logic [7:0] a;
        string s;
      } test;
    test x;
    initial begin;
        x = '{a: '1, s: "test"};
        $display(x.s);
        $finish;
    end
endmodule
```

**Error:**
```
%Error: Internal Error: ../V3Number.cpp:2392: Number operation called with non-string argument: '8'hff"
                                                                                    : ... In instance top
x = '{a: '1, s: "test"};
             ^
```

**Version:**
_git master:_ _Verilator 4.225 devel rev v4.224-49-ge0b61cea_


**Notes:**
The issue "Internal error on string parameter in latest master #3215" seems similar but the fix did not hit this one

Any information on what might be happening would be much appreciated
